# Convert to AAC (MP4) with variable bitrate (constant quality)
# "-q 100" is default, you can change it up and down (higher is more quality, but larger file)
faac -w -q 100 <infile>.wav <outfile>.m4a

# Convert to AAC (MP4) with constant bitrate (variable quality)
# # "-b 192" is an example, you can change it up and down (higher is more quality, but larger file)
faac -w -b 192 <infile>.wav <outfile>.m4a
